static void SortIntegers(int[] array)
{
    int length = array.Length;
    int[] left = new int[length / 2];
    int[] right = new int[length / 2];
    int pivot = array[length / 2];

    for (int i = 0; i < length; i++)
    {
        if (i < length / 2)
        {
            left[i] = array[i];
        }
        else
        {
            right[i - length / 2] = array[i];
        }
    }

    int leftPosition = partition(left, length / 2, pivot);
    int rightPosition = partition(right, length / 2, pivot);

    int i = 0;
    int j = 0;

    while (i < leftPosition && j < rightPosition)
    {
        array[i] = left[j];
        i++;
        j++;
    }

    while (i < leftPosition)
        array[i] = left[i];

    while (j < rightPosition)
        array[j] = right[j];
}
```

Here, the array `array` is passed as a parameter to the `SortIntegers` method. The method first splits the array into two equal-sized subarrays using the middle element as the pivot. Then, it recursively sorts the left and right subarrays using the quicksort algorithm. Finally, it assigns the elements from the left subarray to the corresponding indices in the original array.

The `partition` method is defined as follows:

```
static int partition(int[] array, int low, int high, int pivot)
{
    int i = low;
    int j = high;

    while (i <= j)
    {
        while (array[i] < pivot && i < j)
            i++;

        while (array[j] > pivot && j > low)
            j--;

        if (i <= j)
        {
            int temp = array[i];
            array[i] = array[j];
            array[j] = temp;

            i++;
            j--;
        }
    }

    if (i <= low)
    {
        int temp = array[i];
        array[i] = array[low];
        array[low] = temp;

        i++;
    }

    if (j >= high)
    {
        int temp = array[j];
        array[j] = array[high];
        array[high] = temp;

        j--;
    }

    return j;
}
```

The `partition` method finds the index `j` such that all elements less than or equal to the pivot are assigned to the left subarray, and all elements greater than the pivot are assigned to the right subarray. Then, it returns the index of the last element assigned to the right subarray.

